Project setup


--Frontend

  - Download Node.js (if not installed)

	- use "npm install" to install vite

	- to run use "npm run dev"

	- make sure to setup a database 


--Backend

  - .NET version 10.0 Visual studio 2026

	- use self-signed certificate (SSL)

	- update connection "DefaultConnection" in appsetting.development.json to your MSSQL server 	

	- For Local Format using window authentication

	"DefaultConnection":Server=your instance;Database=Note_application;Trusted_Connection=True;Integrated Security=True  add this if need SSL (TrustServerCertificate=True)"
    
	-For Local Format using SQL Server authentication
   
	"DefaultConnection": "Server=Your Instance;Database=Note_application;User Id=your id;Password=your paaword;Trusted_Connection=True;Integrated Security=True;TrustServerCertificate=True"


-- database

  - Database provided in GitHub is are for MSSQL 2022 version 17.00

	- you can back up the database 

	(if not able to restore database make sure to create database)

	- create a new database in MSSQL name: Note_application

	run these queries in the Note_application

-User table:

CREATE TABLE [dbo].[Users](
  [UserId] [int] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,
  [UserName] [nvarchar](100) NOT NULL,
  [Password] [nvarchar](255) NOT NULL,
  [CreatedAt] [datetime] NOT NULL)

-Notes table 

CREATE TABLE [dbo].[Notes](
  [NoteId] [int] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,
  [Title] [nvarchar](200) NOT NULL,
  [Content] [nvarchar](max) NOT NULL,
  [UserId] [int] NOT NULL,
  [CreatedAt] [datetime] NOT NULL,
  [UpdatedAt] [datetime] NULL)
